         <abstract>
            <p>Ethiopian manuscripts often contains a collection of text around each Gospel transmitted as part of the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1560Gospel">Four Gospels</ref>.
               These may include: an introductory part containing <ref target="#BiographyLuke">Biography</ref>, <ref target="#TituliLuke">Tituli (the number of Tituli may vary)</ref>, <ref target="#EusebianSectionsLuke">Eusebian Sections</ref>, the actual <ref type="work"  corresp="LIT2713Luke">Gospel</ref> (which may be preceded by <ref target="#LukeGospelHeadline">a headline</ref>), and the <ref target="#PostscriptLuke">Postscript</ref>.
            </p>
         </abstract>
